                     <additions>
                        <list>
                           <item xml:id="e1">
                              <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>
                         record of a debt of three schillings, including witnesses; written in ink pen by a later hand.
                       </item>
                           <item xml:id="e2">
                              <locus target="#iiv(erso)"/>
                         a list of the Gǝ‘ǝz alphabet and numbers, in black ink.
                         </item>
                           <item xml:id="e3">
                              <locus target="#iiv(erso)"/>
                        list of the astrological signs.
                        </item>
                           <item xml:id="a1">
                              <locus target="#135v"/>
                              <desc type="GuestText">
                                 <title ref="LIT3851Hassab"> Excerpt from the Computus on how Dǝmeṭros found the calculation of the epact <foreign xml:lang="gez">የጥንተ፡ አብቅቴ፡ ይትመጣ፡ ድሜጥሮስ፡ በመዓልት፡ ፯፡ ሱባዔ፡ በሌሊት፡</foreign>.</title>
                              </desc>
                           </item>
                           <item xml:id="e4">
                              <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>
                            title of the book in pencil
                        </item>
                           <item xml:id="e5">
                              <locus target="#ir #iir"/>
                          blank
                          </item>
                           <item xml:id="e6">
                              <ref target="#ms_i1.1"/>
                            Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters.
                          </item>
                           <item xml:id="e7">
                              <locus target="#45v"/> bottom four lines of text have been scraped off and three lines of text written in their place.
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e8">
                              <locus target="#103v"/>
                            Upper margin, name of owner<desc type="OwnershipNote">
                                 <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሐና፡</foreign>
                              </desc>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e9">
                              <ref target="#136v"/>
                            prepared to receive painting, but never completed.
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e10">
                            scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#24v #60r #99v #120v #133r #135v"/>;
                            and lines of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#11v #15v #69v #94v"/>;
                            and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) in red and black ink marking the location where the text is to be inserted <locus target="#129v"/>, line 4 and <locus target="#133r"/>, line 16);
                            erasure markings are visible <locus target="#59v"/>; text has been removed <locus target="#51r #65v #100v"/>
                          </item>
                          <item xml:id="e11">
                            the scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                              Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the
                              codex combined with an appropriate script size.
                              But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below
                              the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid
                              having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#19v #20r"/>).
                          </item>

                        </list>
